# Human-in-the-Loop Workflow

## Step Execution

- Uses `suspend()` to pause execution until human approval.
- Returns `{ approved: false }` while waiting and `{ approved: true }` once resumed.

```ts
execute: async ({ inputData, resumeData, suspend }) => {
  if (!resumeData?.approved) {
    await suspend({ reason: "Needs approval" });
    return { approved: false };
  }
  return { approved: true };
}
```

### Resume Later

- Detects `suspended` status and resumes the workflow with `resumeData`.

```ts
// Resume later
if (result.status === "suspended") {
  await run.resume({
    step: result.suspended[0],
    resumeData: { approved: true }
  });
}
```

