# Error Recovery with Suspension

- Suspends the step when encountering a `RATE_LIMIT` error so the workflow can be retried later.
- Continues to throw non-recoverable errors.

```ts
execute: async ({ suspend }) => {
  try {
    return await apiCall();
  } catch (error) {
    if (error.code === 'RATE_LIMIT') {
      await suspend({ 
        reason: "Rate limited",
        retryAfter: error.retryAfter 
      });
      return { status: "paused" };
    }
    throw error;
  }
}
```

